title: For Sale:  Chinese, Type 56, SKS
postcontent:
Very early Chinese Type 56 SKS, used in very good condition, no rust or pitting anywhere. If you know Chinese SKSs then you know that they began making them in 1956 hence the name “type 56.” This rifle has a 5 digit serial # and does not have a factory/arsenal marking. A serial # of less than 6 digits is dated 1956 or earlier. Some SKS collectors call these “ghost” rifles and they are speculated to be some of the very first Chinese made SKS at the Jianshe Arsenal 26. The bluing has been worn off on the metal that is above wood probably from lots of cleaning and handling. Chrome lined bore looks excellent, no pitting. I cleaned off all the cosmoline and fired approx 100 rds. through it no problems. The serial numbers on receiver, bolt and trigger group all match. The receiver cover is a Russian Tula replacement cover. I bought this rifle back in 2013. It was speculated that this batch came from Albania. This is a very collectable early Chinese example. More info on Chinese SKS: http://yooperj.com/SKS-24.htm

title: For Sale:  Arsenal SLR-95. Bulgarian milled AK47.
postcontent:
The Bulgarian SLR-95 is a milled receiver AK variant that was imported by D.I.G. VA, of Virginia into the United States from 1994 to 1998 only. It is a post ban version of the original Russian Type 3 Milled AK47, produced by Arsenal of Bulgaria. The SLR-95 is a 100% made-in-Bulgaria (unlike the SAM series of Arsenal rifles produced today). The barrel on the SLR-95 is a Steyr cold hammer forged, chrome lined barrel that per Arsenals website is serviceable until 15,000 rounds. 

The rifle is in very good condition, and the fit and finish are superb. There is absolutely ZERO sight canting (not many AKS are factory produced like this), the action and feel of the rifle is incredibly smooth (due to the milled receiver), and trigger pull is very crisp (due to the double hook trigger). The round count on the rifle is at 1,500. The barrel is only at 10% of its usable life, and the rifling is perfect. The rifle has been non permanently modified to accept a standard two tang buttstock in place of the thumbhole "sporter" stock it had originally came with. Installing the "sporter" buttstock that came on the rifle is as easy as removing the buttstock , lower tang, and pistol grip in its place. Then just insert and install said thumbhole stock. 

I have added a "target sight" front post (thinner to see more precise shots at greater distances), and a krebs safety selector (not pictured). This rifle hits a torso sized steel target at 300 yards all day. The rifle does come standard with the SLR series pinned on muzzle brake, which is very effective in mitigating muzzle rise and felt recoil. 

Below are the specifications from Arsenal Bulgarias website. 
Arsenal AK 47 SLR-95 Milled AK-47 Arsenal-SLR-95.
Steyr Technology Cold Hammer Forged, Chrome lined Barrel. Service life, 15000 rounds.
System of operation - Gas, Semi-automatic fire only. 
Bolt type - Rotating. 
Weight (unloaded) - 7.6 lbs.

Length, overall - 35.43 inches. 
Accepts 30 round magazines or drums with virtually zero mag wobble.

Sights, rear - Tangent leaf, graduated from 100 to 800 meters. 
Cartridge - 7.62 x 39 Soviet M43.

I live in the NW apart of town. Buyer of the rifle must fill out a bill of sale and have a valid NV drivers license, or have a blue card, or CCW. The price for the rifle is $925. postcontent: The new M6-SL is a replacement of our base model M6 rifle of old. The SL, which stands for 'stretch-lightweight', incoroprates everything a shooter needs in a quality light-weight base model rifle. Price and weight were the most important factors when developing the SL. With the M6-SL, LWRCI has brought to the market the lightest factory piston driven rifle to date. The SL comes standard with Magpul furniture. A MOE mid-length handguard, MOE Stock, and MOE pistol grip provide excellent handling characteristics, while minimizing added weight. The SL utilizes the 'stretch' or mid-length piston system, providing a more direct recoil impulse for faster follow-up shots. The most distinct feature of the SL is the barrel. The barrel still utilizes LWRCI's NiCorr surface conversion technology on a cold-hammer-forged barrel, but the barrel is of a smaller diameter to reduce weight. The SL comes standard with the EXO (nickel-boron) plated one piece bolt carrier and the EXO coated enhanced fire control group. The SL also comes standard with a Daniel Defense A1.5 fixed rear sight and a fixed A2 front sight post. The SL is a great addition to the LWRCI family of rifles. It provides users with an extremely lightweight rifle that incorporates our patented short-stroke piston operating system, has all of the advanced coatings that make our rifles the best in the world, and does so at an entry level price.
